  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "<!-- Please only use this template for submitting enhancement requests -->\r\n\r\n**What would you like to be added**:\r\n\r\nCurrently, the `Status` field on `CustomResourceDefinitions` must be explicitly set to their zero-values due to the fact that they are not tagged `omitempty`.\r\n\r\nRef:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/controller-tools/blob/0dd9d80ad4b98900d6066141dd4233354b25e3f3/pkg/crd/spec.go#L154\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\n\r\nIf using a system that automatically compares the provided configuration to the current, it will produce a diff on the updated status after creation. In addition, making sure to explicitly set to zero-values is not the best user experience.\r\n\r\nI am happy to provide the fix if this change is approved!\r\n\r\n/cc @DirectXMan12 \r\n\r\n/sig api-machinery\r\n/area custom-resources\r\n",
